        <msIdentifier>DCCCXLIII</msIdentifier>
        <physDesc>Paper, about 6 5/8 in. by 5, consisting of 70 leaves (Add. 14,728, foll. 138—207). The quires, signed with letters, are 7 in number. There are from 15 to 20 lines in each page. This manuscript is written in a fair hand of the xiiithcent. The writing on the fly-leaves, foll. 138 and 205 b—207, is different, but not much later. The contents are—</physDesc>
        <msItem>
